reviewText: Superb series, intelligent, witty, and far more insightful about the politics of power than many serious and self-righteous US TV shows. Brits know that humour can be a far more incisive scalpel than preachy, moralistic stories with twists, whistles and forced drama. And they're supposed to be the pompous ones...
I think This series probably illumine s how our own politics function. Very enlightening. Six more words required. Is this enough?
